        "paragraph_index": 2,
        "text": "### Notable Exception: π-Acceptor / Soft Ligands\n\nThe data show that **2,2′-bipyridyl** — a classic π-acceptor ligand — gives essentially **identical** ML log β values for Fe³⁺ and Fe²⁺ (both 4.2). For the higher complexes (ML₂, ML₃), Fe²⁺ is well known to become *more* stable than Fe³⁺ with bipyridyl, consistent with the extraordinary stability of [Fe(bipy)₃]²⁺. This pattern is expected to extend to other soft/π-accepting ligands such as 1,10-phenanthroline.",
